\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Place a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/grill-pan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 grill pan}} over medium-high heat or preheat a gas or charcoal grill.\
Place the garlic and parsley in the bowl of a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/food-processor/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 food processor}}. Pulse until finely chopped. Add the ground {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chuck/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chuck}}, Parmesan cheese, tomato paste, salt, and pepper. Pulse until ingredients are combined. Form the mixture into 9 patties. Place the burgers on the grill and cook for 4 to 5 minutes each side.\
Brush the cut side of each roll with the olive oil and toast on the grill for 1 to 2 minutes until slightly golden.\
To serve, place 1 mini burger on the bottom half of each of the rolls. Place 1 slice of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/taleggio/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Taleggio}} cheese on top of the burgers. Place the basil leaf on top of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cheese/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cheese}} and cover with the top half. Serve.\
